	* clients/android/res/layout/menu.xml: Replaced selfmade button icons and
	  adjusted the style a bit.

	* clients/android/res/drawable/settings_button.png,
	  clients/android/res/drawable/tvguide_button.png,
	  clients/android/res/drawable/tvrecorder_button.png: Replaced buttons
	  icons with nice ones.

2011-09-13  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/res/drawable/main_menu_button_state.xml: New. An Android
	  selector that is used to give users an optical feedback while pressing
	  buttons in the main menu.

	* clients/android/res/layout/menu.xml: Make use of the
	  main_menu_button_state selector.

	* clients/android/res/drawable/main_menu_button_pressed.png: New. This
	  image is displayed if the user presses a button in the main menu.

2011-09-13  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/MainMenu.java: New.
	  This activity is now launched at application start. It uses the menu.xml
	  UI declaration which displays buttons for each user interface.

	* clients/android/res/layout/menu.xml: UI definition for the MainMenu.
	  There is a button displayed for each activity that should be visible to
	  the user.

	* clients/android/AndroidManifest.xml: Registered MainMenu activity as
	  startup activity.

	* clients/android/res/values/strings.xml: New strings for the MainMenu.

	* clients/android/res/drawable/main_menu_button.png: Background image for
	  buttons in the MainMenu.

	* clients/android/res/drawable/settings_button.png,
	  clients/android/res/drawable/tvguide_button.png,
	  clients/android/res/drawable/tvrecorder_button.png: Button images for
	  TvRecorder, TvGuide and TvRecorderSettings activities.

	  TODO: Create nice button images! The current ones are really ugly!

2011-09-08  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/receivers/TvGuideUpdateReceiver.java:
	  New. A BroadcastReceiver that is used to update the database (TvShows)
	  based on the network state and the configuration.

	* clients/android/AndroidManifest.xml: Registered the
	  TvGuideUpdateReceiver with an IntentFilter to listen for network state
	  changes.

	* clients/android/res/xml/preferences.xml: Added further config options to
	  prevent updates if no wifi connection is available or if roaming is
	  active.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/Config.java: Added
	  new config keys.

	* clients/android/res/values/strings.xml: Added new strings for the two
	  config options.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java: Do
	  not start the TvGuideUpdateService. The update mechanism uses the
	  TvGuideUpdateReceiver. This should minimize battery costs.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/database/ChannelSQLiteHelper.java:
	  Implemented the needsUpdate() method. An update is required if
	    last update time + INTERVAL <= now.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/TvGuideDataStore.java:
	  Adapted the call of ChannelSQLiteHelper.needsUpdate().

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/database/SQLiteProvider.java:
	  Added a new table that stores the last update times for each table.

2011-09-05  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/services/TvGuideUpdateService.java:
	  New. This service is update to update the TvGuide stored in the database
	  in the background of the application. The process is executed frequently -
	  its update interval is adjustable in the settings dialog. This service
	  implements an OnSharedPreferencesChangedListener to change the update
	  interval or to terminate the service if the auto-update flag is removed
	  from configuration.

	* clients/android/AndroidManifest.xml: Registered the TvGuideUpdateService.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/Config.java: Added
	  new methods that retrieve boolean, double and integer values from
	  configuration.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java:
	  Start the TvGuideUpdateService when the relevant config option is set.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/setup/TvRecorderSettings.java:
	  Added a handler that listens to tv guide update relevant config changes.
	  If the auto-update option is set, the TvGuideUpdateService is started.

2011-09-01  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/utils/JSONUtils.java:
	  New function that returns a JSON representation of a record Job.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RecordServerResource.java:
	  The RecordResource is no longer able to take a serialized Job - instead,
	  this resource will now take a JSON representation of a Job.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/TvGuide.java:
	  Implemented the method to record a tv show.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/listeners/RecordJobListener.java:
	  Adapted the code to start a record Job - the HTTP communication now uses
	  the JSON representation instead of serialized Java objects.

2011-09-01  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/utils/JSONUtils.java:
	  Added a flag to toJSON() that forces to export old tv shows as well to
	  JSON. Otherwise, only future tv shows are included in the JSON
	  representation.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvGuideServerResource.java:
	  This service only provides tv shows that take place in the future (this
	  should minimize the HTTP traffic a bit).

2011-09-01  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/res/xml/preferences.xml: New. A layout description for
	  the config options required/supported by TvRecorder Android client.

	* M clients/android/res/values/strings.xml: New strings for the
	  preferences activity.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/Config.java: Renamed
	  the config keys specific to the server. Furthermore, there is a new
	  config option to enable/disable authentication.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java: Do
	  not check if there the required config entries are already set by the
	  user.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/setup/TvRecorderSettings.java:
	  Removed the whole layout stuff - use the preference layout description
	  defined in preferences.xml instead (which is the recommended way
	  anyway).

2011-09-01  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java:
	  Removed code to initialize the environment. This seems to be the wrong
	  way - it seems to lead to incorrect dates/times.

2011-08-31  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/database/SQLiteProvider.java:
	  New. This class provides SQLite database support. All necessary tables
	  are created while initializing an instance of this class if no such
	  tables exist.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/database/ChannelSQLiteHelper.java:
	  New. This class provides some methods to save/load channels to/from
	  SQLite database.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/TvGuideDataStore.java:
	  New. The TvGuideDataStore hides the code to fetch the data (from
	  database or from server via HTTP). All classes that require TvGuide
	  information should use this datastore to retrieve the data.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/TvGuide.java:
	  We have two datastores now: the TvRecorder server and the SQLite
	  database provided by SQLiteProvider. New data (TV shows) is only fetched
	  from server if the last update is one day (or longer) ago.

2011-08-30  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/libs/org.restlet.lib.org.json-2.0.jar,
	  clients/android/libs/org.restlet.ext.json.jar: Added dependencies to ext
	  JSON extension (TvGuide service is the first service that uses the JSON
	  representation).

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/Config.java: Added
	  functions that return the default locale and time zone used for the JVM.
	  
	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java:
	  Initialize the environment (locale and timezone).

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/TvGuide.java:
	  The TvGuide service serves the data as JSON, so we gonna read the tv
	  guide's JSON representation now instead of serialized Java objects.

2011-08-30  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/objects/ChannelWithTvGuide.java:
	  Return an empty Collection if no TvShow are given instead of "null".

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/utils/JSONUtils.java:
	  Put long value of start/end time of a TvShow into JSON representation of
	  a TvShow.

2011-08-29  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/ChannelsServerResource.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RecordServerResource.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvRecorderResource.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rss/RssReader.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/tvguide/xmltv/XmlTvShowUpdater.java:
	  Removed needless imports.

2011-08-29  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/conf/config.xml: Added config options for TvGuide update-interval,
	 xmltv file and the date format used in the xmltv file.

	* server/pom.xml: Added dependency to Restlet's JSON extension.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvGuideServerResource.java:
	  This service returns its data as JSON string now.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/tvguide/xmltv/XmlTvShowUpdater.java:
	  Read the new options from `config.xml` and parse date strings properly.

2011-08-29  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/pom.xml: Added dependency to Restlet's JSON extension.

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/objects/ChannelWithTvGuide.java,
	  common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/objects/TvShow.java:
	  Added missing getter methods to fulfill Java Bean requirements.

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/utils/DateUtils.java:
	  New function to parse date strings.

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/utils/JSONUtils.java:
	  New. Helper class that currently provides functions to write channels
	  and tv shows to JSON.

2011-08-25  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/objects/TvShow.java:
	  Added a new constructor that also takes an end date.

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/utils/XMLUtils.java:
	  Added a method that allows reading Documents from File.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/config/Config.java:
	  Added XPath expressions that point to the dateformat used for reading
	  the datetime strings in tvguide and the interval the application should
	  update the tvguide.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvRecorderServer.java:
	  Use the XmlTvShowManager to provide tvguide information.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/tvguide/xmltv/XmlTvShowManager.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/tvguide/xmltv/XmlTvShowUpdater.java:
	  New. These classes provide tvguide information from XMLTV files.

2011-07-22  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/conf/config.xml: The output-directory is now configurable in
	  /server/record/output-directory/text().

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/config/Config.java:
	  Added an XPath expression that returns the output directory from config.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/utils/CmdProducer.java:
	  Removed the default output directory constant. This static path
	  shouldn't be used any longer.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/utils/MPlayerCmdProducer.java:
	  Use the Config to determine the output directory for records.

2011-07-19  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rss/RssReader.java:
	  Workaround: subtract 1 hour after parsing dates. Dates are shifted for 1
	  hour to the future after parsing. This will avoid wrong dates. But, it
	  would be better to store dates in UTC only!

2011-07-19  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/TvGuide.java:
	  Handle communication exceptions. The app will no longer crash if no
	  connection to the server could be established.

	* clients/android/res/values/strings.xml: Added errors messages if no
	  channels have been found.

2011-07-18  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java: Use
	  Android native DatePickerDialog and TimePickerDialog.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/DatePickerDialog.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/TimePickerDialog.java:
	  Removed.

2011-06-06  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvshow/TvShowDetail.java,
	  clients/android/res/layout/tvshowdetail.xml: New. An activity that
	  displays information of a specific tv show. The data that should be
	  displayed is put as extra data into the intent.

	* clients/android/res/values/strings.xml: Added a label for the
	  TvShowDetail activity.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/TvGuide.java:
	  Put information about a tv show to the intent and start the TvShowDetail
	  activity if the "detail" item of the context menu is selected.

	* clients/android/AndroidManifest.xml: Registered the new activity.

2011-06-06  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/tvguide/TvShowManager.java:
	  New. The interface that describe a TvShowManager. Currently, we have a
	  RssTvShowManager, but maybe there will be another manager some time ago.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/tvguide/rss/RssTvShowManager.java:
	  Implements the TvShowManager interface now.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RestApp.java:
	  Registered the TvShowManager in the context.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvRecorderResource.java:
	  New method that returns the current TvShowManager.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/tvguide/rss/RssTvShowUpdater.java:
	  Adapted the default update interval - set to 1 hour.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvRecorderServer.java:
	  Start the RssTvShowManager as thread.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvGuideServerResource.java:
	  New. A REST resource that returns the tv shows of the channels supported
	  by the TvShowManager.

	  NOTE: We need to sync the RSS channels with the supported channels by
	  the server (dvb-*).

2011-05-31  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/res/layout/tvrecorder.xml: New. A layout for the simple
	  form to add jobs. The layout has been defined in Java code before. This
	  is done in this xml layout now which is the reommended way to define
	  layouts in android.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java:
	  Removed the layout stuff from java code. Added UI listener to change
	  component values and start recording a tv show.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/listeners/RecordJobListener.java:
	  This listener will now fetch its necessary values from TvRecorder
	  activity.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/AddJobForm.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/DateTimeWidget.java:
	  Removed, because the layout stuff is done in XML files.

2011-05-30  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/res/values/strings.xml: Added strings for the tvguide
	  context menu.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/TvGuide.java:
	  Removed the UI layout creation. This work is done using XML files that
	  describe the layout of this activity.

	* clients/android/res/layout/tvguide.xml: New. A layout description for
	  the tvguide. Currently, the tvguide consists of a combo box to select
	  the displayed tv channel and a list view that displays the tv shows of
	  the selected channel.

	* clients/android/res/menu/tvguide_list_context.xml: New. A layout
	  description for the context menu of the tv guide. Currently, there are
	  options to record a tv show or to display a details of a tv show.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/TvShowsAdapter.java,
	  clients/android/res/layout/tvguide_list.xml: Changed the IDs of the text
	  fields in tv guide list.

2011-05-24  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/AndroidManifest.xml: Registered the TvGuide as new
	  activity for the TvRecorder android client.

	* clients/android/res/values/strings.xml: Added i18n strings for the
	  TvGuide activity.

	* clients/android/res/layout/list_item.xml: Added a better representation
	  for list views than the default one is.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java: The
	  TvGuide activity is reachable from the context menu now.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/RetrieveChannelsHandler.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/TvGuideUpdateEvent.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/TvGuideUpdateListener.java:
	  Interfaces and classes for a listener mechanism which is necessary to
	  fetch the TvGuide from tvrecorder server and update the UI after
	  finishing this work.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/tvguide/TvGuide.java:
	  New. This activity has the goal to show all supported channels and a tv
	  show listing for each of those channels.

2011-05-24  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/objects/Channel.java,
	  common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/objects/TvShow.java:
	  Improved the string representation of toString() which is necessary to
	  put these objects into spinner and list views.

2011-05-23  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/rest/TvGuideResource.java:
	  New. The interface of a REST resource that should provide channels with
	  tv shows.

2011-05-23  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* .hgignore: New. A ignore file for mercurial.

2011-05-23  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/contrib/update.sh: New. A shell script to start the
	  RssTvShowManager as standalone application. Currently used for
	  development reason.

2011-05-23  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/tvguide/TvShowUpdateEvent.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/tvguide/TvShowUpdateListener.java:
	  New. Interfaces necessary for a listener mechanism which is used to listen to
	  changes after TV channels have been updated (~> Tv shows).

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/tvguide/TvShowUpdater.java:
	  New. This interfaces describes the update master to update tv channel
	  guides.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/tvguide/rss/RssTvShowManager.java:
	  New. This update manager is specialized to handle tv guides from RSS
	  feeds.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/tvguide/rss/RssTvShowUpdater.java:
	  New. This updater fetches tv guide information from RSS feeds and
	  returns ChannelWithTvGuide objects.

	  NOTE: This updater should be threaded, but there are problems existing
	  that avoid using more than a single thread. And this single threads
	  needs to sleep a while between fetching the data of two channels from rss
	  feeds :-/ Otherwise - without sleeping - all channels will have the same
	  tv shows...

2011-05-23  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/objects/ChannelWithTvGuide.java:
	  New. This special channel class provides information about the tv shows
	  of this channel.

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/objects/TvShow.java:
	  New. This model class represents a tv show with title, description and a
	  start date at minimum.

2011-05-23  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/rss/RssFeed.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/rss/RssItem.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/rss/RssReader.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/rss/RssXMLUtils.java:
	  Removed. I decided to fetch the rss feeds on the server - this is pretty
	  slow on the client :-/ In addition to that, other clients would need
	  that code as well...

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rss/RssFeed.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rss/RssItem.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rss/RssReader.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rss/RssXMLUtils.java:
	  New. Moved from android client.

2011-05-20  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/model/ChannelUpdateJob.java:
	  New. This class contains a channel and an URL that is used to update the
	  channel with tv listing information.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/model/ChannelWithListing.java:
	  New. A special channel that knows about its tv shows.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/model/TvShow.java:
	  New. A tv show with title, description, start and end date.

2011-05-19  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/rss/RssReader.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/rss/RssFeed.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/rss/RssItem.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/rss/RssXMLUtils.java: New. A
	  rss reader and required model classes.

2011-05-19  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/utils/XMLUtils.java:
	  New. A helper class that support some basic functions to work with XML
	  files.

2011-03-08  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/conf/config.xml: Added an example block that shows the usage of
	  HTTP BasicAuth.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/config/Config.java:
	  Added XPath expressions that points to auth type, name and password.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvRecorderServer.java:
	  Added code to provide HTTP BasicAuth. The configuration is queried to
	  get to know about the auth type, the username and its password.

	  NOTE: The only authentication type that is currently supported is the
	  HTTP BasicAuth!

2011-03-07  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/res/values/arrays.xml: Added two further config options
	  for HTTP BasicAuth.

	* clients/android/res/values/strings.xml: Added i18n strings for the HTTP
	  BasicAuth config options.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/Config.java: Added
	  method for retrieving the login and password used for authentication.

	  NOTE: The Config class contains a method that retrieves a
	  ClientResource, now. This method should be used everywhere where a
	  ClientResource is needed, because that resource is prepared for
	  authentication (if configured).

2011-03-24  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/pom.xml,
	  server/pom.xml: Fixed broken Restlet dependency - the repository structure
	  of the Restlet maven repository has changed.

2011-01-13  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* NEWS: A NEWS file that contains the major changes for each release.

	=== RELEASE 0.1 ====


2011-01-13  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/activities/setup/TvRecorderSettings.java:
	  New. An activity that allows the user to edit the settings of the
	  TvRecorder. It will show a list with all settings defined in arrays.xml.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/KeyValueItem.java:
	  New. This LinearLayout will show a key/value pair with a button on the
	  right.
	  TODO: Improve the layout!

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/TextDialog.java:
	  This dialog will show a textfield and a button to submit the dialog. It
	  defines an interface OnOkListener that is called after hitting the OK
	  button. The listener can be set using a setOnOkListener() method.

	* clients/android/AndroidManifest.xml: Added the new activity.

	* clients/android/res/values/strings.xml: Added new strings for the
	  settings.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/Config.java: The server
	  url and port are no longer taken from config.xml. Now, we query the
	  SharedPreferences for fetching the settings.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java: At the
	  application start, we make sure, that all necessary settings are defined.
	  If this is not the case, the TvRecorderSettings activity is opened.

	* clients/android/res/values/arrays.xml: New. Defines the necessary settings
	  of the TvRecorder. Currently, there are just two major settings: the
	  server url and port number.

	* clients/android/res/values/config.xml: Removed.

2011-01-11  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/AddJobForm.java:
	  Changed the padding of the name textfield. The text is no longer clipped.

2011-01-11  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/listeners/RecordJobListener.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/AddJobForm.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/DatePickerDialog.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/TimePickerDialog.java:
	  Removed hard coded strings. Use the texts from resource files instead.
	  This allows us to support more languages (I18N).

	* clients/android/res/values/strings.xml: The strings that occur in the user
	  interface.

2011-01-08  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/utils/DateUtils.java:
	  Added a new function that checks, if two time ranges collide.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/backend/Backend.java:
	  Added a new method that retrieves all queued jobs. The job creation is
	  moved to an own helper class that makes it able to reuse the same code to
	  create jobs loaded from database.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvRecorderResource.java:
	  New. This ServerResource implements some basic methods to retrieve jobs,
	  channels or other attributes stored in the context.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/ChannelsServerResource.java:
	  Extends TvRecorderResource that implements the getChannels() method.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RecordServerResource.java:
	  Extends TvRecorderResource and added a new constraint before adding new
	  jobs: the job retrieved by the client may not collide with an existing
	  job.

2011-01-08  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RecordServerResource.java:
	  The incoming job request is validated before an at job is created. The job
	  must at least fulfill the following two conditions:
	    - the start date is smaller than the end date
	    - the channel must be available in the server

	  NOTE: we should further check if there are no collisions with other jobs
	  that are already started/created.

2011-01-08  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/utils/DateUtils.java:
	  Removed. The client uses the DateUtils class from common package now.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/listeners/RecordJobListener.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/DateTimeWidget.java:
	  Both classes use the DateUtils from common package now.

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/utils/DateUtils.java:
	  Added new date format strings used by the client.

2011-01-07  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/ChannelsServerResource.java:
	  This resource returns the real channel list from context now - the dummy
	  values are removed.

2011-01-07  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RestApp.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvRecorderServer.java:
	  The channels defined in the channels configuration file are available in
	  the context of the RestApp now. They are retrievable via the constant
	  TvRecorderServer.CHANNELS_KEY.

2011-01-07  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/utils/DVBSChannelsParser.java:
	  Bugfix: avoided a NullPointerException if no lines are returned from
	  FileUtils while parsing the channels configuration file.

2011-01-07  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/utils/XMLUtils.java:
	  Introduced a helper class to work with XML documents.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/config/Config.java:
	  Introduced this class as a central point for querying configuration
	  settings.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/backend/DBConnection.java:
	  The path to the database file is queried from Config now. If no path is
	  configured, or an error occured while reading that config option, the
	  default path is used (tvrecorder.db).

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvRecorderServer.java:
	  The port that the server is listening on is read from Config now. If no
	  port is configured, or an error occured while reading that option, the
	  default port (8282) is used.

	* server/conf/config.xml: A default config file. It contains the port that
	  the server should listen on, the path to the sqlite database file and the
	  path to the channels configuration file.

2011-01-06  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/utils/FileUtils.java:
	  Added a new function that retrieves the lines of a file as String array.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/utils/DVBSChannelsParser.java:
	  This class represents a parser that is used to extract the channels of a
	  MPlayer DVB-S configuration file.

2011-01-06  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RecordServerResource.java: 
	  After a job has arrived here, a new At job is created. This job executes a
	  command (currently for MPlayer) that starts recording the job.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/ChannelsServerResource.java:
	  Changed the keys of the channels.

	* server/contrib/stop_records.sh: The default shell script that is executed
	  by At jobs to stop MPlayer recording.

	* server/jobs/do-not-delete-me,
	  server/records/do-not-delete-me: Directories for storing jobs and records.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/utils/AtJobCreator.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/utils/StartAtJobCreator.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/utils/StopAtJobCreator.java:
	  An abstract base class and two subclasses. AtJobCreators have the task to
	  create new At jobs. StartAtJobCreator should be used to create an At job
	  to start recording, the StopAtJobCreator should be used to stop these
	  recordings.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/utils/CmdProducer.java.
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/utils/MPlayerCmdProducer.java:
	  The CmdProducer interface describes a single method to create command
	  lines. MPlayerCmdProducer produces a concrete command line that that
	  starts recording with usage of Mplayer.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/utils/FileUtils.java:
	  A helper class for working with files.

2011-01-05  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/utils/DateUtils.java:
	  A helper class that should make it easier to work with Date objects.

2011-01-03  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RestApp.java: The
	  backend is available via the Context's attribute map now ('backend').

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvRecorderServer.java:
	  Injected the Backend into the RestApp.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RecordServerResource.java:
	  Incoming jobs are saved to database now. But the real recording stuff is
	  still missing!

2011-01-03  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/pom.xml: Added a dependency to Xerial's SQLiteJDBC
	  driver (version 3.7.2).

	* server/docs/schema.sql: A simple schema definition for the job table.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/backend/Backend.java:
	  The backend. Currently, there are two methods defined to load all jobs
	  from database and insert new jobs into it.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/backend/DBConnection.java:
	  This class is used to retrieve a database connection.

2010-12-27  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java: The
	  TvRecorder Activity has now an OptionsMenu with two items - the target of
	  "Quit" is to stop the application, "Settings" should open a window to
	  change some basic settings (like the server url). "Settings" is not
	  implemented yet!

2010-12-25  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/listeners/RecordJobListener.java:
	  Now, we make sure, that the start date is smaller than the end date of the
	  record job. Otherwise, an warn dialog is shown and no job is sent to the
	  server.

2010-12-25  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RecordServerResource.java:
	  Removed a debug line that has been commited by accident.

2010-12-25  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/objects/Job.java: The
	  job stores its start and end time as Date objects now, because there have
	  been problems while serialization or deserialization in client or server.
	  The result was, that no job could be transfered between client and server.

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RecordServerResource.java:
	  Added some more debug statements and validate the job objects at the
	  beginning of add() to make sure, that it is not null.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/AddJobForm.java:
	  This form's getChannel() method returns a real Channel object instead of
	  a string representation of the Channel.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/listeners/RecordJobListener.java:
	  Some adjustments based on the changes mentioned above.

2010-12-11  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/DatePickerDialog.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/TimePickerDialog.java:
	  New. Dialogs to select a date and a time. Both contain a special interface
	  that describes a method that is fired if a date or a time was selected in
	  the widget.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/DateTimeWidget.java:
	  Removed the onTouch event and added two OnClickListener to the date and
	  time fields. A click on the date field will open a DatePickerDialog, a
	  click on the time field will open a TimePickerDialog.


2010-12-11  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/rest/ChannelsResource.java,
	  common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/rest/RecordResource.java:
	  Added the resource path to the interfaces.

	* clients/android/res/values/config.xml: A configuration file where
	  necessary settings shuould be defined. Currently, important things are
	  remote server url and server port.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/Config.java: New. This
	  class defines some functions that retrieve application settings.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java:
	  Removed the path definitions for the ChannelsResource and RecordResource.
	  The definitions are useless now: the relative pathes are defined in the
	  interfaces and the server url is retrievable by Config.

	* clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/handlers/RetrieveChannelsHandler.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/listeners/RecordJobListener.java:
	  The necessary urls are taken from Config now.


2010-12-11  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* clients/android/AndroidManifest.xml,
	  clients/android/build.properties,
	  clients/android/build.xml,
	  clients/android/default.properties,
	  clients/android/libs/org.restlet-2.0snapshot.jar,
	  clients/android/libs/tvrecorder-common-0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar,
	  clients/android/local.properties,
	  clients/android/res/drawable-hdpi/icon.png,
	  clients/android/res/drawable-ldpi/icon.png,
	  clients/android/res/drawable-mdpi/icon.png,
	  clients/android/res/layout/main.xml,
	  clients/android/res/values/strings.xml,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/TvRecorder.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/handlers/RetrieveChannelsHandler.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/listeners/RecordJobListener.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/AddJobForm.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/ui/DateTimeWidget.java,
	  clients/android/src/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/client/utils/DateUtils.java:
	  The initial checkin of an Android client. Currently, the gui consists of a
	  single AddJobForm. This form contains two DateTimeWidgets to adjust the
	  start and end time, a select box to select the channel, a text field to
	  specify a name of the job and a button to add the defined job.

	  Note: The creation of a new job is currently not implemented.


2010-12-11  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/App.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/ChannelsServerResource.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RecordServerResource.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/RestApp.java,
	  server/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/server/rest/TvRecorderServer.java:
	  The initial checkin of the server. The server represents a HTTP server
	  with some REST interfaces to retrieve supported channels and add new jobs
	  for recording.

	* server/LICENSE: The server is distributed under the GPL v3.

	* server/conf/log4j.properties: A logging configuration for Log4J.

	* server/contrib/run.sh: A bash script to start the server.

	* server/pom.xml: The maven configuration of the server. Currently, there
	  are dependencies to JUnit, Restet and the common package.


2010-12-11  Ingo Weinzierl <ingo_weinzierl@web.de>

	* common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/objects/Channel.java,
	  common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/objects/Job.java,
	  common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/rest/ChannelsResource.java,
	  common/src/main/java/de/inselhome/tvrecorder/common/rest/RecordResource.java:
	  The initial commit of the common package. This package contains objects
	  that are used for the communication between clients and server. Both,
	  client and server, should make use of this package!

	* common/pom.xml: The maven configuration of the common package.
	  Currently, there are dependencies to JUnit and Restlet.

	* common/LICENSE: This package is distributed under the GPL v3.
